		       Niagara Falls is by far the most popular day trip destination for Torontonians. 
		       In addition to the world-famous waterfalls, there are also wineries and other spectacular natural surroundings.</p>
			<p>
			   If you are looking for beaches, Wasaga Beach about a 2 hr drive away is the longest freshwater beach in the world.
			</p>
			<p>
			   Famous for its annual Stratford Festival, the quaint little town of Stratford on the Avon river is worth visiting as well.
